'''HMAS ''Pirie'' (J189/B249/A123)''', named for the city of [[Port Pirie, South Australia|Port Pirie]] in [[South Australia]], was a [[Bathurst class corvette]] built by the Broken Hill Propriety Shipyard at [[Whyalla, South Australia|Whyalla]] in South Australia, launched on [[3 December]] [[1941]] by Mrs. H. T. Kleeman, wife of the Whyalla superintendent of BHP, and commissioned on [[10 October]] [[1942]].

''Pirie'' was present in [[Tokyo Bay]] on [[Victory over Japan Day]] ([[2 September]] [[1945]]), when the [[Japanese Instrument of Surrender]] was signed. <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.navy.mil/faqs/faq69-2.htm |title=Allied Ships Present in Tokyo Bay During the Surrender Ceremony, 2 September 1945 |accessdate=2007-01-13 |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date=27 May 2005|publisher=Naval Historical Center - U.S. Navy|quote=Taken from ''Commander in Chief, U.S. Pacific Fleet and Pacific Ocean Areas (CINCPAC/CINCPOA) A16-3/FF12 Serial 0395, 11 February 1946: Report of Surrender and Occupation of Japan''}}</ref>

HMAS ''Pirie'' paid off on [[5 April]] [[1946]], was transferred to [[Turkey]] and renamed ''Amasra''.

